        <div class="num">The founder — Oliver Hudson</div>
        <h2>I've always lived <em>through sport.</em></h2>
        <p>I'm Oliver — an ex-professional tennis player. Sport has been my entire life: the training, the matches, the recovery, the obsession with marginal gains. And for as long as I can remember I've been trying to find products that actually help with hydration and recovery — the two things that separate a great session from a wrecked one.</p>
        <p>Nothing on the shelf was doing the job. Sports drinks were 90% sugar. Electrolyte sachets under-dosed sodium by 4–6×. Nothing addressed the cognitive side of fatigue. So I went looking for something I'd actually want to drink every day — and bring to the market for the millions of people who play sport like I do.</p>
        <p>That search led me to <strong>9× fire-roasted bamboo salt</strong> — a 1,000-year-old Korean tradition where sea salt is packed into bamboo stalks, sealed with clay, and fired at 1,500°C. Nine times. The result: <strong>pH 12, 70+ trace minerals, hydroxyl ions you can't get from any other salt source.</strong></p>
        <p>The catch: most "bamboo salt" on the market is roasted once or twice and called done. We track down the <strong>highest grade — the rare 9× version no other electrolyte sachet or hydration drink uses</strong> — straight from the kilns where they still do it the traditional way.</p>
        <p>That's the story of how IONIQ came to life. One sachet. The hydration, recovery and clean energy I wish I'd had on court.</p>
        <blockquote class="pull">
          "If it's not what I'd put in my own bottle before a match, it doesn't make it into IONIQ."
          <span class="by">— Oliver Hudson, founder</span>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
